255Es1_%26ref_url%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fm.economictimes.com%252Fmagazines%252Fpanache%252Fhandwriting-a-lost-art-zohos-rs-50000-cr-mans-fear-sparks-fiery-internet-debate%252Farticleshow%252F123420895.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epredicted%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20X%20that%20%26quot%3Bhandwriting%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20lost%20art.%26quot%3B%20Generative%20AI%20was%20expected%20to%20speed%20up%20the%20decline%20of%20pen-and-paper%20writing%2C%20not%20trigger%20its%20return%20to%20the%20halls%20of%20higher%20learning.%20Perhaps%20unsurprisingly%2C%20it's%20been%20a%20bumpy%20ride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20one%20Ivy%20League%20professor%20recently%20confessed%20at%20our%20mutual%20friend's%20get-together%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20handwriting%20is%20really%2C%20really%2C%20%3Cem%3Ereally%3C%2Fem%3E%20bad.%26quot%3B%20Just%20trying%20to%20read%20student%20assignments%20for%20grading%20purposes%20has%20become%20a%20whole%20new%20headache%2C%20doubling%20the%20time%20the%20task%20requires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20road%20from%20perfect%20penmanship%20to%20chicken%20scratch%20in%20America%20is%20windy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHandwriting%20used%20to%20be%20a%20pillar%20of%20the%20American%20educational%20curriculum%2C%20one%20of%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bthree%20Rs%26quot%3B%20alongside%20%26quot%3Breading%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3B'rithmetic.%26quot%3B%20What%20that%20curriculum%20looked%20like%20at%20any%20given%20time%20had%20a%20lot%20to%20do%20with%20the%20labor-force%20needs%20of%20the%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20US%20was%20shaping%20itself%20into%20the%20world's%20industrial%20superpower%20in%20the%20mid-19th%20century%2C%20Platt%20Rogers%20Spencer%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bfather%20of%20American%20handwriting%2C%26quot%3B%20popularized%20his%20intricate%20%26quot%3BSpencerian%26quot%3B%20script%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20developing%20meticulous%2C%20detail-focused%20future%20workers.%20His%20approach%20became%20the%20standard%20in%20US%20classrooms%20until%20the%20early%2020th%20century%2C%20when%20it%20was%20replaced%20by%20the%20more%20utilitarian%20Palmer%20Method%20%E2%80%94%20a%20cursive%20technique%20that%20prioritized%20speed%20and%20legibility%20for%20the%20machine%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20by%20the%20late%201970s%2C%20handwriting%20instruction%20was%20already%20on%20the%20decline%2C%20says%20Jonathan%20Dubay%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Handwriting%20Success.%20Electric%20typewriters%20had%20become%20widely%20available%2C%20and%20teaching%20kids%20how%20to%20write%20had%20always%20been%20a%20hassle.%20%26quot%3BTeachers%20had%20to%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20on%20it%2C%20kids%20weren't%20remembering%20how%20to%20do%20it%2C%20and%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20recidivism.%20It%20wasn't%20working.%26quot%3B%20That's%20when%20Dubay's%20mother%2C%20Inga%2C%20joined%20forces%20with%20the%20calligraphy%20instructor%20Barbara%20Getty%20to%20develop%20a%20handwriting%20curriculum%20for%20elementary%20school%20students%20using%20their%20patented%20Getty-Dubay%20Italic%2C%20which%20sought%20to%20marry%20the%20ease%20of%20printing%20with%20the%20speed%20of%20writing%20in%20cursive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Getty-Dubay%20system%20gained%20traction%2C%20but%20not%20enough%20to%20reverse%20handwriting's%20trajectory%20of%20neglect.%20By%20the%20late-2000s%2C%20articles%20in%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20and%20TIME%20mourned%20the%20demise%20of%20%26quot%3Ba%20legible%20hand%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20in%20cursive%2C%20which%20American%20schools%20had%20largely%20stopped%20bothering%20to%20teach%20altogether.%20In%20the%20years%20that%20followed%2C%20the%20ubiquity%20of%20smartphones%20seemed%20like%20the%20final%20nail%20in%20the%20coffin%20for%20the%20handwritten%20word.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%20ChatGPT%20and%20other%20AI%20text%20generators%20have%20immediately%20proved%20to%20be%20high-tech%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatgpt-homework-cheating-machine-sam-altman-openai-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomework-cheating%20machines%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20some%20professors%20tinkered%20with%20AI-detection%20tools%20to%20root%20out%20plagiarism%2C%20others%20opted%20to%20go%20analog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20May%2C%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%20a%20surge%20in%20Blue%20Book%20sales%20across%20several%20US%20universities%20as%20evidence%20of%20the%20trend.%20Roaring%20Spring%20Paper%20Products%2C%20the%20company%20that%20makes%20Blue%20Books%2C%20confirms%20year-over-year%20sales%20increases%20since%20ChatGPT%20became%20widely%20available%20in%20late%202022.%20However%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20tells%20me%20that%20global%20sales%20are%20still%20well%20below%20their%20pre-pandemic%20numbers%2C%20explaining%20that%20the%20switch%20to%20online%20learning%20hastened%20a%20takeover%20of%20online%20exams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECOVID%20also%20sped%20up%20the%20deterioration%20of%20handwriting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristopher%20Hamner%2C%20a%20history%20professor%20at%20George%20Mason%20University%2C%20recalls%20a%20time%20earlier%20in%20his%20teaching%20career%20when%20students%20had%20%26quot%3Battractive%26quot%3B%20handwriting.%20These%20days%2C%20he%20says%20it's%20more%20often%20%26quot%3Bappalling%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20points%20to%20the%20pandemic%20as%20a%20culprit.%20Today's%20undergrads%20were%20in%20middle%20and%20high%20school%20when%20the%20world%20went%20into%20lockdown%20and%20learning%20went%20online%2C%20which%20cost%20students%20precious%20handwriting%20practice%20as%20teens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20practice%20shows.%20%26quot%3BAbout%20a%20quarter%20print%20neatly%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20are%20hard%20to%20read%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Hamner%2C%20who%20brought%20back%20Blue%20Book%20exams%20last%20year.%20%26quot%3BI%20tell%20them%2C%20'If%20I%20can't%20read%20it%2C%20you%20don't%20get%20points.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Schoemann%2C%20a%20computer%20science%20professor%20at%20the%20College%20of%20Charleston%2C%20has%20heard%20the%20horror%20stories.%20She's%20chosen%20to%20pivot%20to%20in-class%20handwritten%20evaluations%20anyway%20following%20a%20%26quot%3Brude%20awakening%26quot%3B%20with%20a%203D%20modeling%20class%20last%20spring.%20Students%20were%20supposed%20to%20build%20an%20outdoor%20scene%20showing%20rain%20or%20snow%20using%20premade%20models%20and%20their%20own%20particle%20effects%3B%20many%20submitted%20nearly%20identical%2C%20low-quality%20gray%20palm%20trees%20with%20nondescript%20particle%20details%20falling%20over%20them.%20When%20Schoemann%20tested%20the%20assignment%20prompt%20in%20ChatGPT%2C%20it%20produced%20the%20same%20output%20the%20students%20had%20turned%20in.%20Though%20the%20writing%20requirements%20are%20fairly%20minimal%20for%20Schoemann's%20courses%2C%20they're%20enough%20to%20generate%20sympathy%20for%20her%20colleagues%20in%20other%20departments.%20%26quot%3BHumanities%20and%20social%20sciences%20faculty%20are%20struggling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20ongoing%20backslide%2C%20general%20interest%20in%20handwriting%20has%20been%20quietly%20percolating%20for%20years.%20Dubay%20has%20seen%20a%20swell%20in%20handwriting-instruction%20app%20sales%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20some%20of%20which%20he%20attributes%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20homeschooling.%20%26quot%3BIn%20general%2C%20parents%20have%20decided%20they%20want%20their%20young%20students%20to%20have%20a%20handwriting%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECursive%20writing%20is%20making%20a%20comeback%20of%20its%20own.%20This%20summer%2C%20Pennsylvania%20legislators%20passed%20a%20bill%20that%20would%20require%20cursive%20handwriting%20instruction%20in%20the%20state's%20public%20schools%2C%20citing%20%26quot%3Bcompelling%20cognitive%2C%20developmental%2C%20and%20practical%20reasons%20for%20ensuring%20students%20have%20at%20least%20a%20basic%20grasp%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20skill.%20If%20the%20bill%20gets%20signed%20into%20law%2C%20Pennsylvania%20will%20become%20the%2026th%20state%20to%20mandate%20teaching%20cursive%20%E2%80%94%20a%20figure%20that's%20nearly%20doubled%20since%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20practical%20reasons%20to%20celebrate%20the%20revival%2C%20such%20as%20preserving%20the%20ability%20to%20read%20archival%20documents%20in%20the%20case%20of%20cursive.%20But%20there%20are%20likely%20cognitive%20benefits%20to%20handwriting%2C%20too%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20form.%20In%20a%202021%20study%20published%20in%20%26quot%3BPsychological%20Science%2C%26quot%3B%20people%20who%20took%20physical%20notes%20absorbed%20and%20remembered%20new%20information%20better%20than%20those%20who%20typed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20are%20drawn%20to%20hand-hewn%20lettering%20for%20the%20same%20reasons%20they%20might%20be%20inclined%20to%20take%20up%20basket-weaving%20or%20buy%20a%20bookcase%20built%20from%20scratch.%20In%20today's%20slick%20screen-filled%20world%2C%20there's%20something%20to%20be%20said%20for%20craftsmanship%2C%20and%20the%20practice%20of%20slowing%20down%20to%20create%20something%20new%20and%20beautiful%20from%20beginning%20to%20end.%20A%20Reddit%20group%20dedicated%20to%20practicing%20and%20improving%20handwriting%20is%20one%20of%20the%20platform's%20largest%20at%20over%201%20million%20members%2C%20while%20TikTok%20and%20YouTube%20boast%20a%20burgeoning%20cadre%20of%20handwriting-focused%20content%20creators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20have%20been%20slow%20to%20get%20the%20memo.%20Apart%20from%20a%20handful%20of%20Blue%20Book%20exams%20in%20college%2C%20I%20probably%20haven't%20handwritten%20at%20length%20since%20middle%20school%20%E2%80%94%20a%20long%2C%20long%20time%20ago.%20But%20I%20did%20take%20physical%20notes%20throughout%20high%20school%20and%20college%2C%20where%20I%20recall%20preferring%20the%20pleasing%20scratch%20of%20a%20mechanical%20pencil%20over%20the%20scratchy%20drag%20of%20ballpoint%20pens.%20So%20when%20it%20came%20time%20to%20draft%20this%20article%2C%20I%20returned%20to%20my%20old%20pal%2C%20the%20Bic%20%232.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20right%20tools%2C%20my%20technique%20was%20sorely%20lacking.%20I%20struggled%20to%20close%20the%20loops%20on%20my%20lower-case%20'A's%20and%20'O's%2C%20which%20made%20them%20both%20look%20like%20the%20letter%20'U.'%20I%20developed%20cramps%20across%20every%20finger%20on%20my%20writing%20hand%2C%20and%20riled%20up%20a%20sports%20injury%20in%20my%20right%20elbow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrustrations%20aside%2C%20writing%20by%20hand%20made%20me%20feel%20more%20plugged%20into%20what%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20express.%20I%20can%20type%20about%20as%20quickly%20as%20I%20can%20think%2C%20which%20means%20I%20often%20don't%20give%20myself%20the%20time%20to%20properly%20think%20through%20a%20point%20before%20putting%20it%20on%20the%20page%20(or%2C%20more%20accurately%2C%20the%20screen).%20I%20wind%20up%20typing%20and%20retyping%20the%20same%20sentences%20and%20paragraphs%20as%20I%20hone%20my%20thinking%20along%20the%20way.%20Handwriting%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%20(right%2C%20in%20my%20case)%2C%20forces%20a%20level%20of%20decisiveness%20that%20I've%20all%20but%20eradicated%20from%20my%20usual%20creative%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTechnology%20can%20make%20answers%20easy%20but%20also%20paralyze%20students%20with%20too%20many%20options%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Russell%20Seidle%2C%20a%20business%20professor%20at%20Suffolk%20University%20in%20Boston%20who%20has%20used%20Blue%20Book%20exams%20in%20his%20classes%20since%202013.%20After%20briefly%20experimenting%20with%20an%20online-first%20approach%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Seidle%20realized%20that%20handwritten%20exams%20developed%20stronger%20reasoning%20skills%20by%20forcing%20students%20to%20commit%20to%20one%20answer%2C%20justify%20it%2C%20and%20show%20how%20they%20got%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20students%20relearning%20to%20digest%20information%20without%20the%20help%20of%20AI%2C%20writing%20by%20hand%20facilitates%20a%20potentially%20transformative%20shift.%20It%20may%20also%20prove%20beneficial%20for%20their%20professional%20futures.%20After%20all%2C%20the%20most%20valuable%20workers%20are%20those%20that%20can%20think%20for%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20or%20not%20that%20process%20involves%20feeding%20the%20right%20prompts%20to%20a%20machine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamner%2C%20the%20history%20professor%2C%20tells%20his%20students%20that%20using%20AI%20for%20reading%20is%20like%20having%20someone%20else%20eat%20your%20ice%20cream%20sundae%20for%20you.%20The%20same%20could%20be%20said%20for%20writing%2C%20a%20process%20of%20coming%20up%20with%20an%20idea%20and%20working%20through%20it%20from%20beginning%20to%20end.%20%26quot%3BThe%20joy%20is%20in%20doing%20it%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BHandwritten%20exercises%20help%20students%20reconnect%20with%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fkelli-maria-korducki%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EKelli%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Korducki%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20journalist%20whose%20work%20focuses%20on%20work%2C%20tech%2C%20and%20culture.%20She's%20based%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprofessors-fighting-ai-handwriting-chatgpt-blue-books-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1763025061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6914fd34e1a9cbb014de17d8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprofessors-fighting-ai-handwriting-chatgpt-blue-books-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Professors%20are%20fighting%20AI%20by%20making%20students%20write%20by%20hand.%20Too%20bad%20it's%20unreadable.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kelli%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Korducki