%20to%20fund%20the%20federal%20government%20through%20January%2030.%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20signed%20the%20bill%20on%20Wednesday%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20sets%20aside%20money%20for%20agencies%20like%20the%20Food%20and%20Drug%20Administration%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fveterans-affairs-musk-doge-opm-email-trump-federal-workers-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Veterans%20Affairs%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2043-day-long%20shutdown%20disrupted%20everything%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-snap-benefits-november-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebenefit%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-flight-delays-could-persist-after-shutdown-ends-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eair%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20employee%20paychecks.%20And%2C%20though%20federal%20agencies%20are%20resuming%20operations%2C%20it%20could%20take%20longer%20for%20Americans'%20lives%20to%20return%20to%20normality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20to%20expect%20as%20the%20shutdown%20comes%20to%20an%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227ccbb579-bce4-4df8-bd09-19faa4fbbf6e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFederal%20workers%20will%20receive%20their%20first%20paycheck%20in%20over%20a%20month%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20federal%20workers%20have%20been%20furloughed%20or%20working%20without%20pay%20since%20October%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20has%20spoken%20with%20over%20two%20dozen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-workers-wallets-paycheck-to-paycheck-government-shutdown-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efederal%20workers%20%3C%2Fa%3Eacross%20various%20agencies%20who%20have%20missed%20paychecks%20since%20the%20shutdown%20began.%20Many%20said%20they%20have%20cut%20back%20on%20expenses%2C%20such%20as%20home%20repairs%2C%20social%20outings%2C%20and%20their%20children's%20activities.%20A%20few%20struggled%20to%20afford%20essentials%20like%20groceries%20and%20rent%2C%20and%20some%20have%20taken%20out%20emergency%20loans%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20paycheck%20pause%20applied%20to%20most%20government%20employees%2C%20except%20for%20lawmakers%2C%20military%2C%20and%20select%20law%20enforcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChecks%20for%20federal%20workers%20and%20contractors%20will%20resume%20with%20the%20government%20reopening.%20Congress'%20spending%20agreement%20also%20guarantees%20that%20these%20employees%20will%20receive%20back%20pay%20for%20hours%20worked%20during%20the%20shutdown%20%E2%80%94%20money%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20previously%20hinted%20it%20may%20not%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20take%20time%20for%20these%20employees%20to%20pay%20off%20loans%20and%20replenish%20savings%20that%20were%20depleted%20in%20recent%20weeks.%20In%20terms%20of%20job%20security%2C%20the%20House-approved%20bills%20require%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20reverse%20any%20staff%20cuts%20made%20during%20the%20shutdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20guess%20it%20was%20a%20bit%20of%20relief%20that%20I%20still%20have%20a%20job%20and%20I%20know%20where%20my%20next%20paycheck%20is%20going%20to%20come%20from%20when%20the%20shutdown%20ends%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20employee%2C%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20ground%20has%20been%20shaken%20beneath%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227ae1c181-db86-4666-bd38-d93362a8e106%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20could%20take%20weeks%20for%20airport%20issues%20to%20be%20resolved%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETravelers%20aren't%20out%20of%20the%20woods%20yet.%20The%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20has%20canceled%20thousands%20of%20flights%20since%20Friday%2C%20when%20government%20officials%20reduced%20flying%20by%2010%25%20at%2040%20US%20airports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELate%20Wednesday%20evening%2C%20the%20US%20Transportation%20Department%20and%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20issued%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transportation.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fus-transportation-secretary-sean-p-duffy-faa-administrator-bryan-bedford-freeze%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoint%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20announcing%20that%20the%20agencies%20would%20freeze%20flight%20reductions%20at%206%25%20following%20positive%20staffing%20trends%20among%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-traffic-controllers-punish-sick-miss-pay-shutdown-sean-duffy-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eair%20traffic%20controllers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Henry%20Harteveldt%2C%20an%20aviation%20strategist%20at%20Atmosphere%20Research%20Group%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20a%20rubber%20band%2C%20so%20it's%20not%20going%20to%20snap%20back.%26quot%3B%20He%20estimates%20that%20it%20could%20take%20one%20to%20two%20weeks%20for%20flight%20schedules%20to%20return%20to%20normal.%20That%20could%20coincide%20with%20the%20busy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthanksgiving-travel-chaos-companies-warn-government-shutdown-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThanksgiving%20travel%20week%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENerdWallet%20travel%20expert%20Sally%20French%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20FAA-mandated%20flight%20cancellations%20make%20it%20harder%20for%20airlines%20to%20quickly%20recover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20shouldn't%20just%20automatically%20assume%20if%20they%20have%20a%20flight%20this%20weekend%2C%20that%20everything%20is%20going%20to%20be%20exactly%20perfect%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20still%20going%20to%20be%20kind%20of%20the%20snowball%20effect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20the%20aviation%20analytics%20company%20Cirium%20shows%20cancellations%20peaked%20on%20Sunday%2C%20with%20about%2010%25%20of%20scheduled%20flights%20canceled.%20However%2C%20it%20said%20things%20were%20improving%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20which%20could%20give%20airlines%20some%20buffer%20to%20catch%20up%20before%20the%20Thanksgiving%20rush.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-visit-sequoia-kings-canyon-national-parks-during-government-shutdown-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENational%20parks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20museums%2C%20and%20historical%20sites%20experienced%20full%20or%20partial%20closures%20during%20the%20shutdown%20and%20will%20now%20reopen%20to%20visitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225215e5da-b2d1-42ce-bce0-9f80071772e6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESNAP%20will%20resume%20for%20millions%20of%20Americans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFood%20stamps%20will%20resume%20as%20normal%20with%20the%20government%20reopen.%20Forty-two%20million%20Americans%20rely%20on%20the%20Supplemental%20Nutrition%20Assistance%20Program%20to%20afford%20groceries%20every%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20last%20weeks%20of%20the%20shutdown%2C%20SNAP%20was%20caught%20in%20a%20legal%20back-and-forth.%20The%20program%20had%20enough%20in%20the%20bank%20for%20October%20benefits%20but%20ran%20out%20of%20money%20to%20pay%20in%20November.%20Federal%20judges%20ordered%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20dip%20into%20contingency%20funds%20to%20fund%20the%20program%2C%20a%20move%20that%20was%20eventually%20paused%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESNAP%20is%20fully%20funded%20at%20the%20federal%20level%20and%20managed%20by%20individual%20states.%20With%20the%20government%20reopen%2C%20states%20will%20be%20able%20to%20send%20full%20November%20benefits%20to%20eligible%20households.%20And%20new%20families%20were%20processed%20into%20the%20SNAP%20system%20during%20the%20shutdown%2C%20so%20anyone%20who%20applied%20for%20benefits%20after%20October%201%20should%20be%20able%20to%20receive%20checks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20forms%20of%20aid%2C%20such%20as%20Temporary%20Assistance%20for%20Needy%20Families%20(TANF)%20and%20the%20Supplemental%20Nutrition%20Program%20for%20Women%2C%20Infants%2C%20and%20Children%20(WIC)%2C%20will%20also%20resume.%20Head%20Start%20childcare%20centers%20should%20also%20receive%20the%20funds%20they%20need%20to%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECongress'%20agreement%20secures%20SNAP%20funding%20through%20most%20of%202026%2C%20though%20the%20program%20will%20still%20see%20changes%20going%20forward.%20New%20work%20requirements%20from%20Trump's%20One%20Big%20Beautiful%20Bill%20Act%20took%20effect%20on%20November%201%20and%20mandate%20that%20nondisabled%20adults%20without%20dependents%20fulfill%20work%20requirements%20until%20they%20reach%20age%2064%20to%20qualify%20for%20aid%2C%20up%20from%20the%20current%20cutoff%20age%20of%2054.%20Funding%20for%20federal%20nutrition%20aid%2C%20such%20as%20SNAP%2C%20is%20also%20set%20to%20be%20reduced%20by%20nearly%20%24200%20billion%20over%20the%20next%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2276938c59-f573-4a40-91b6-fd1fcded488f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMarketplace%20health%20insurance%20costs%20will%20spike%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHealthcare%20spending%20was%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%202025%20shutdown.%20Democrats%20called%20for%20the%20extension%20of%20enhanced%20Affordable%20Care%20Act%20subsidies%20initially%20implemented%20in%202021%20%E2%80%94%20which%20alleviate%20healthcare%20costs%20for%20millions%20of%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20Americans%20on%20Marketplace%20plans%20%E2%80%94%20beyond%20their%20December%2031%20expiration%20date.%20The%20subsidies%20were%20not%20extended%20under%20the%20current%20agreement%2C%20though%20the%20Senate%20will%20vote%20again%20on%20the%20issue%20in%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemocratic%20leaders%20also%20pushed%20for%20the%20reversal%20of%20Medicaid%20funding%20changes%20made%20under%20Trump's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-spending-bill-student-loans-cap-graduate-school-doctor-lawyer-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOne%20Big%20Beautiful%20Bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20Act%2C%20which%20could%20cause%20millions%20of%20low-income%20Americans%20to%20lose%20access%20to%20health%20insurance.%20This%20proposal%20was%20not%20included%20in%20the%20final%20spending%20bill%2C%20and%20Trump's%20changes%20will%20remain%20in%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20open%20enrollment%20beginning%20in%20November%2C%20people%20on%20marketplace%20plans%20could%20see%20a%20staggering%20increase%20in%20their%20expected%202026%20healthcare%20costs.%20A%20KFF%20analysis%20found%20that%20the%20expiration%20of%20enhanced%20ACA%20tax%20credits%20will%20spike%20out-of-pocket%20premiums%20for%20marketplace%20enrollees%20by%20an%20average%20of%20over%2075%25%2C%20with%20insurers%20expecting%20that%20healthier%20enrollees%20will%20drop%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUpdate%3A%20November%2012%2C%202025%20%E2%80%94%20This%20story%20was%20published%20after%20the%20Congressional%20vote%20on%20the%20bill%2C%20before%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20signed%20it.%20It%20has%20been%20updated%20to%20reflect%20the%20most%20current%20information%20at%20press%20time.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fend-of-government-shutdown-what-it-means-airports-snap-aca-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1763002051000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6914d7ffabd5e944effa9918%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fend-of-government-shutdown-what-it-means-airports-snap-aca-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20longest%20shutdown%20in%20US%20history%20set%20to%20end%2C%20but%20it%20could%20take%20time%20for%20airports%2C%20benefit%20programs%2C%20and%20federal%20workers'%20finances%20to%20recover.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22allisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%20(Allie%20Kelly%2CTaylor%20Rains%2CDominick%20Reuter%2CKatherine%20Tangalakis-Lippert)%22