%20a%20penny%20is%20worth%20one%20cent%20while%20in%20circulation%2C%20each%20coin%20actually%20costs%203.69%20cents%20to%20make%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usmint.gov%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Fusmint%2Freports%2F2024-annual-report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20US%20Mint's%202024%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20up%20from%201.42%20cents%20per%20penny%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Mint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20the%20US%20Mint%20was%20burning%20millions%20of%20dollars%20every%20year%20just%20to%20keep%20the%20penny%20alive.%20(A%20US%20Mint%20FAQ%20said%20estimates%20put%20the%20expected%20savings%20at%20roughly%20%2456%20million%20a%20year.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20pennies%20are%20annoying%20to%20use.%20With%20inflation%20steadily%20rising%2C%20the%20buying%20power%20of%20the%20humble%20penny%20has%20plummeted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWant%20to%20buy%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzegna-1100-dollar-shoes-wall-street-cant-get-enough-of-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehottest%20sneakers%20on%20Wall%20Street%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Hope%20you%20brought%20a%20bag%2C%20because%20you'll%20need%20to%20hand%20over%20110%2C000%20pennies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20getting%20yourself%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-cava-sweetgreen-genz-millennials-eating-out-less-sales-earnings-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eslop%20bowl%20for%20lunch%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20in%20the%20range%20of%201%2C700%20pennies%2C%20which%20would%20weigh%20over%209%20pounds%2C%20roughly%20the%20weight%20of%20a%20(healthy%20but%20large)%20newborn%20baby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20the%20White%20House's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-elon-musk-penny-wasteful-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%20set%20its%20sights%20on%20the%20penny%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20fans%20of%20common%20sense%20were%20cheering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20worried%20about%20what%20could%20happen%20after%20the%20US%20loses%20the%20penny%2C%20fret%20not%3A%20we've%20axed%20coins%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarting%20in%201793%2C%20the%20US%20minted%20a%20half-cent%20coin%20with%20an%20image%20of%20Lady%20Liberty%20on%20its%20face.%20Yet%20America%20killed%20that%20off%20with%20the%20Coinage%20Act%20of%201857%2C%20and%20the%20nation's%20economy%20has%20turned%20out%20pretty%20OK%20since%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECan%20the%20Trump%20administration%20unilaterally%20kill%20the%20penny%3F%20It's%20unclear.%20Congress%20could%20step%20in%20to%20fight%20for%20the%20penny's%20future%2C%20but%20so%20far%2C%20lawmakers%20from%20both%20parties%20have%20praised%20the%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20getting%20rid%20of%20the%20penny%20was%20a%20cost-saving%20move%2C%20some%20retailers%20are%20concerned%20about%20what%20comes%20next.%20Pennies%20are%20still%20legal%20tender%2C%20but%20there'll%20be%20fewer%20and%20fewer%20of%20them%20in%20circulation%20each%20year%20as%20the%20copper%20coins%20get%20lost%20in%20couch%20cushions%20and%20laundry%20machines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Retail%20Industry%20Leaders%20Association%20said%20businesses%20want%20guidance%20from%20Congress%20about%20what%20to%20do%20now%20as%20they%20run%20out%20of%20pennies.%20The%20business%20group%20also%20wants%20clarity%20on%20pricing.%20Do%20they%20round%20up%20to%20the%20nearest%20nickel%3F%20Round%20down%20and%20lose%20money%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRetailers%20recognize%20the%20federal%20government's%20decision%20to%20discontinue%20the%20penny%2C%20due%20to%20the%20potential%20for%20cost%20savings%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20organization%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rila.org%2Fblog%2F2025%2F11%2Fretailers-face-penny-shortages-call-for-federal-ac%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20in%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20the%20speed%20of%20the%20phase-out%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20formal%20guidance%20from%20the%20administration%20%E2%80%94%20and%20no%20action%20from%20Congress%20since%20the%20shutdown%20%E2%80%94have%20created%20significant%20challenges%20for%20retailers%20and%20all%20businesses%20that%20accept%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20US%20should%20take%20notes%20from%20its%20neighbor%20to%20the%20north.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECanada%20minted%20its%20last%20penny%20in%202012%2C%20but%20staged%20a%20multi-year%20effort%20to%20educate%20Canadians%20on%20how%20to%20turn%20in%20their%20coins%2C%20round%20up%20the%20more%20than%206%20billion%20pennies%20in%20circulation%2C%20and%20bring%20them%20to%20plants%20to%20harvest%20their%20copper%20and%20zinc%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mint.ca%2Fen%2Fblog%2F2022-06-legacy-of-the-penny%3Fsrsltid%3DAfmBOorX-Jzhe5WR8I-DdfuUdc6QyV7xQrxjNbnj5S7dwVAcAHZZrX4d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20its%20Mint%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20we%20had%20established%20processes%2C%20relationships%20with%20the%20%5Bfinancial%20institutions%5D%20and%20%5Barmored%20car%20companies%5D%20along%20with%20a%20digital%20platform%20helped%20us%20ensure%20we%20had%20a%20successful%20penny%20removal%20campaign%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Anthony%20Rotondo%2C%20Canadian%20Circulation%20Senior%20Manager%20at%20the%20Canadian%20Mint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20there's%20hope%20yet%20for%20the%20US%20to%20truly%20embrace%20a%20bright%20and%20prosperous%20%E2%80%94%20and%20penniless%20%E2%80%94%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flast-us-penny-minted-good-riddance-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1762989173000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6915019ae1a9cbb014de1840%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flast-us-penny-minted-good-riddance-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20White%20House%20DOGE%20was%20right%3A%20the%20penny%20has%20been%20a%20drain%20on%20the%20economy%20and%20should%20have%20been%20phased%20out%20long%20ago.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22psquire%40insider.com%20(Paul%20Squire)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A70%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flast-us-penny-minted-good-riddance-2025-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%20AI%20startup%20powering%20Meta%20and%20OpenAI%20cut%20thousands%20of%20workers%20%26amp%3Bmdash%3B%20then%20offered%20them%20a%20similar%20project%20for%20less%20money%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222133%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brendan%20Foody%2C%20CEO%2C%20Mercor%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F691510efe1a9cbb014de1962%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrendan%20Foody%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20Mercor.%3Cp%3ELester%20Cohen%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Breakthrough%20Prize%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMercor%20ended%20a%20major%20AI%20training%20project%20for%20Meta%2C%20cutting%20thousands%20of%20contract%20data%20labelers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EContractors%20who%20were%20cut%20loose%20said%20they%20were%20then%20offered%20similar%20work%20on%20another%20project%20for%20lower%20pay.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20data%20labeling%20industry%20has%20faced%20widespread%20cuts%2C%20with%20pay%20rates%20dropping%20across%20major%20AI%20firms.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMercor%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20helps%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20train%20their%20AI%20models%2C%20told%20thousands%20of%20its%20contract%20workers%20this%20week%20that%20they%20would%20no%20longer%20be%20working%20on%20a%20large%20project%20for%20Meta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20people%20working%20on%20the%20project%2C%20codenamed%20Musen%2C%20were%20told%20it%20was%20ending%20due%20to%20%26quot%3Bproject%20scope%20changes%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20an%20email%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20Soon%20after%2C%20contractors%20were%20offered%20work%20on%20a%20similar%20new%20project%20named%20Nova%2C%20which%20would%20pay%20%2416%20an%20hour%20%E2%80%94%20%245%20less%20than%20the%20hourly%20rate%20for%20Musen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMercor%2C%20which%20was%20founded%20by%20three%20Thiel%20fellows%20and%20recently%20valued%20at%20%2410%20billion%2C%20is%20part%20of%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-training-companies-startups-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindustry%20of%20data-labeling%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20are%20powering%20the%20AI%20boom.%20Companies%20such%20as%20Meta%20and%20OpenAI%20hire%20these%20firms%2C%20which%20use%20humans%20to%20tag%20and%20categorize%20data%20such%20as%20text%20and%20videos%20to%20improve%20the%20reliability%20of%20AI%20models%20and%20chatbots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%205%2C000%20people%20were%20working%20on%20the%20Musen%20project%20at%20its%20peak%2C%20according%20to%20two%20people%20who%20worked%20on%20it.%20The%20news%20came%20as%20a%20surprise%20because%20they%20had%20recently%20been%20told%20the%20Musen%20project%20would%20run%20until%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20according%20to%20several%20contractors%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Mercor%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20information%20was%20%26quot%3Binaccurate%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20what%20details%20the%20company%20objected%20to.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Meta%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20transparent%20throughout%20the%20duration%20of%20the%20opportunity%20(role%20descriptions%2C%20onboarding%20materials%2C%20etc.)%20that%20this%20is%20temporary%2C%20project-based%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Mercor%20spokesperson%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cd425fc1-f164-4753-afa9-f7cf1c1e8e4f%5C%22%3EProject%20end%20'took%20everyone%20by%20surprise'%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Meta%20invested%20%2414.3%20billion%20in%20Scale%20AI%20earlier%20this%20year%20and%20hired%20its%20CEO%2C%20Mercor%20and%20other%20labeling%20companies%20scooped%20up%20more%20business%20from%20clients%20that%20cut%20their%20ties%20with%20Scale.%20In%20June%2C%20Mercor's%20head%20of%20product%2C%20Osvald%20Nitski%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it%20works%20with%20six%20of%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscale-ai-meta-big-tech-rivals-poach-contractors-clients-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMagnificent%20Seven%26quot%3B%20tech%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20is%20picking%20up%20projects%20from%20clients%20leaving%20Scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmercor-pays-million-per-day-human-contractors-training-ai-ceo-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMercor%20also%20said%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20manages%20over%2030%2C000%20contractors%20and%20pays%20over%20%241.5%20million%20a%20day%20to%20its%20workforce%20of%20human%20trainers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContractors%20working%20on%20the%20Meta%20project%20carried%20out%20a%20variety%20of%20tasks%2C%20including%20evaluating%20prompts%20between%20models%20to%20rank%20which%20was%20better.%20One%20of%20them%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20Musen%20project%20had%20been%20running%20for%20several%20months%20but%20was%20often%20paused%20and%20restarted%20to%20accommodate%20contractors%20working%20in%20different%20time%20zones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20kept%20stressing%20how%20happy%20the%20client%20was%20and%20how%20it%20got%20extended%20until%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20person%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20to%20then%20do%20this%20major%20switch%20up%20before%20the%20holidays%20took%20everyone%20by%20surprise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scrapped%20Mercor%20project%20was%20first%20reported%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%