0%26quot%3Bcreate%20a%20single%2C%20efficient%20grocery%20business%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Beliminate%20duplicate%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225328%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Whole%20Foods%20Market%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6913e30162a04500b316364e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223501%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhole%20Foods%20Market%3Cp%3ERichard%20B.%20Levine%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20also%20launched%20an%20internal%20project%20called%20%26quot%3BFusion%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20delivers%20grocery%20products%20from%20Fresh%20warehouses%20and%20stores%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Whole%20Foods%20stores%2C%20according%20to%20another%20internal%20document.%20That%20service%20launched%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Amazon%20unveiled%20plans%20for%20a%20new%20Whole%20Foods%20store%20concept%20that%20would%20stock%20everyday%20items%2C%20such%20as%20Goldfish%20crackers%20and%20Tide%20detergent%2C%20in%20a%20microfulfillment%20center%20next%20to%20its%20retail%20locations.%20That%20store%2C%20which%20more%20tightly%20aligns%20the%20two%20businesses%2C%20recently%20went%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22154c17da-1263-4556-a4b9-1b68d09bcd04%5C%22%3E'Flying%20formation'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Amazon's%202017%20acquisition%2C%20Whole%20Foods%20employees%20have%20voiced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhole-foods-john-mackey-amazon-acquisition-marriage-divorce-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworries%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20losing%20the%20brand's%20identity%20and%20the%20values%20that%20once%20defined%20its%20appeal.%20That%20has%20created%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazons-physical-stores-business-struggles-to-grow-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etension%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20the%20two%20companies%20and%20a%20fraught%20working%20rel